{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> οἴκ-ησις</b>, εως, ἡ, <br /> <b>the act of dwelling</b> or <b>inhabiting,</b> ἡ κατὰ τὴν χώραν αὐτόνομος οἴ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 2.16; ποιέεσθαι οἴ. ὑπὸ γῆν 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 3.102 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; κοινωνεῖν τῆς οἰ. to share in <b>residence,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Politica” 1275a8; διάθεσιν.. πρὸς οἴκησιν δεδωκώς “Sammelb.” 5357.6 (5th c.AD) \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>right of residence,</b> εἶναι αὐτοῖς.. οἴκησιν Ἀθήνησι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “IG” 12.110.31. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>management, administration,</b> πόλεως [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Minos” 321b. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>house, dwelling,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 9.94, 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 1009, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Philoctetes” 31, 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 321d, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 1.124, etc.; ἔγκτησις γᾶς καὶ οἰκήσιος “Delph.” 3(1).359 (3rd c.BC) \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>residence</b> of a satrap, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 3.2.1 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; στρατηγικὴ οἴ. Wilcken [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “Chr.” 385.67 (3rd c.BC) \">Refs 3rd c.BC+</a>]; κατασκαφὴς οἴ. ἀείφρουρος, of the grave, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 892; εἰς τὴν ἀΐδιον οἴ. 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Agesilaus” 11.16 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>lair</b> of beasts, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Cyn.” 13.14, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Protagoras” 320e \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; bird's <b>nest,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Historia Animalium” 614b31 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, of the scattered <b>dwellings</b> of people not yet collected in cities, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.88, compare οἰκέω 5th c.BC: Bacchylides Lyricus 11; ἡ περὶ τὰ τῶν πόλεών τε καὶ οἰκήσεων διακόσμησις 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Symposium” 209a, compare “Lg.” 681a \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]: but the distinction is not always observed, compare[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\"[prev. work] 685a, etc. \">Refs</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__III</b></Level2> <b>inhabited district,</b> διὰ τὸ τὴν οἴ. κεῖσθαι ταύτην πρὸς ἄρκτον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Meteorologica” 363a3 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; <b>inhabited portion of the globe,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Hippocrates Medicus cited in 2nd c.AD: Galenus Medicus “περὶ τῶν ἰδίων βιβλίων” 6, 1st c.BC: Geminus Astronomicus 5.43, +others, 2nd c.AD: Cleomedes Astronomus 1.5, 2nd c.AD: Ptolemaeus Mathematicus “Tetrabiblos” 76, 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 4.58, +others \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__IV</b></Level2> <b>family, household</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “GDI” 1582 (from Dodona). \">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G8451","accentedUnicode":"οἴκησις","shortDef":"place of abode","mediumDef":"place of abode","stepGloss":"place of abode","stepTransliteration":"oikēsis","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}